123
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:14,380
by a wolf?–the boys turn to crime, eventually
stealing some of Amulius’s sheep.

124
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:18,789
Remus is captured and taken before Amulius
for trial.

125
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:24,160
At this point, Faustulus reveals to Romulus
the brothers’ true identities.

126
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:29,790
Romulus, in good criminal-hero fashion, sets
off for Alba Longa to get revenge on his great-uncle

127
00:08:29,790 --> 00:08:30,790
the king.

128
00:08:30,790 --> 00:08:34,130
Romulus kills Amulius and rescues Remus.

129
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:38,520
He gives the vacant throne to Amulius’s
grandfather Numitor and then the twins go

130
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:42,960
off to found their own city, which brings
us to the Thoughtbubble.

131
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:48,610
Romulus and Remus decide where they were abandoned,
